##Meituan takeout is up

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

By Dawn

Editor | Aalen

In mid February, some merchants reported that Meituan takeaway had problems with a sudden increase in commission, monopoly operations and Unfair competition. A number of associations in Chongqing, Sichuan, Hebei, Yunnan and other places are calling for Meituan and other delivery platforms to lower their commissions.

During the outbreak, canteens were closed, and takeout became a lifeline for the restaurant industry. Businesses trying to make the switch from offline to online are finding it hard to do take out. Commission rate is too high, is the biggest takeaway difficulties. The level of the rate, and take-out business directly linked to the death line, each increase a point, means that the revenue of the business reduced a point.

At the end of last year, some merchants received the notice of Meituan takeout, to increase its take-out commission from 16% to 21% . At the same time, after 9 pm, in addition to the fixed delivery fee, there is an additional charge. Under the new policy, some merchants can hardly make a profit.

Some merchants raised the take-out price, but found that the order quantity subsequently reduced, so in Meituan take-out APP advertising, in order to recover lost orders. Finally, the final accounting, found or not to make money.

Meituan did not formally respond to the businessman's complaint. At the end of February, Meituan upgraded its previous "Spring Breeze Action" by exempting takeaway merchants in Wuhan from a one-month commission and extending their annual fee by two months, and extending it to Hubei Province by another month.

However, Meituan is having a hard time even after it raised its commission rate to 20 per cent in some regions. From 2013 to the present, Meituan takeout has lost money for five consecutive years, until the second quarter of 2019, Meituan takeout in the operating level to turn around. In 2018, it paid $30.5 billion to 2.7 million meituan riders.

Just profit less than half a year, to catch up with the Black Swan epidemic, Meituan takeaway or once again into the mud loss.

On the one hand, after the listing of profit pressure, on the other hand, the epidemic of small and medium-sized businesses under the joint resistance. Meituan is facing a dilemma over the commission.

The Package Commission of Meituan

"before the epidemic, the commission went up by five points, and now the most difficult thing for take-out is the High Commission, " said Ding Sheng, the owner of a fast food restaurant in Guangzhou that has moved into Meituan.

Since last year, Ding Sheng has found takeout increasingly difficult. On the one hand, the operating costs of offline physical stores, such as rental Labor, while the take-out Platform Commission is also increasing.

According to Ding Sheng, according to different regions, Meituan Commission is divided into flowing commission and food commission, can also be divided into commission receivable and paid commission. Commission methods are much the same, all times a fixed rate.

The problem is, this commission rate is going up every year.

From the initial 8% , to around 16% in 2018, to now some areas as high as 20% , meituan takeaway commission rate, has reached the break-even line of some small and medium-sized businesses. MEITUAN's cash-flow rate rose from 12% in 2017 to 14% in 2019. That means Meituan takes 14 yuan for every 100 yuan order.

The increase in commission rates is only one part of the story, and the number of items charged is growing.

Beijing restaurant chain Meituan and ele.me, both with a 16% commission rate, have been set up. In Meituan takeout, its commission is based on the amount paid after the discount, multiplied by a 16% commission rate, guaranteed commission of 5 yuan.

With its brand, its commission rate has not risen in the past year. But from the end of last year, the local Meituan marketing manager began to recommend the policy of "expanding the business circle" , the scope of distribution is expanded, but there is an additional charge. "expanding the business circle means increasing the commission, and the distribution cost of our single order has increased, " said Jing Liu, the director. He found that in the past, bad weather, the platform will reduce the scope of distribution, he can report to the platform to apply to expand the business circle, distribution fees will not rise, but must now increase the payment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image / visual China

On top of that, platform subsidies, to which it has become accustomed, are being reduced.

"The biggest feeling last year was that there was a big reduction in free resources, whether it was distribution subsidies or advertising resources, all of which had to be paid for, " he said. He used to be able to get some free promotion resources by getting to know Meituan's marketing manager, but "now you have to play with money. ".

In Meituan takeout, merchants can buy ads on the front page and rank. Ding Sheng found that after ranking, sometimes orders doubled on a single day, but once advertising budgets fell, orders immediately shrank.

In the second half of last year, Meituan had 5.9 million active merchants and more than 30 million daily orders. In such a volume, commission is no longer the platform's only way of monetizing.

"Meituan and ele.me are very smart now, and they don't really do anything about commission, because it's about looking at a bone to make money, which makes a lot of businesses feel cold, and no one can make money, so they do it in other ways, " Liu said. In addition to commission, to distribution, marketing, data as a representative of value-added services package, platform derived from more cash channels.

As a metaphor, "It's like you're the landlord, and I wouldn't like it if you came in every once in a while and raised my rent, but you could do something else, like remodel our heating, upgrade our wiring, renovate our furniture. Of course, there is a charge for that."

Squeezed profits

The increase in commission rates is intended to make up for business losses.

In the past five years, Meituan has accumulated losses of nearly 20 billion yuan. It was not until the second quarter of 2019 that Meituan made its first profit.

Food and beverage delivery, to hotels, hotels, bicycles and other new business, Meituan is the three business modules. TAKEOUT is the base dish, accounting for more than half of GMV's and revenue. But the long-term loss of the delivery business, the rider is the largest cost.

According to Meituan financial report, we can calculate such an account. A paid 45 yuan (Meituan 2019 Q3 average customer price of 45 yuan) take-out orders, in 20% commission rate, Meituan commission of 9 yuan. But this 9 Yuan Commission, Meituan to give about 7 yuan to riders, the remaining 2 yuan to be used to share servers, research and development, marketing and other costs. After deducting the rest of the money, Meituan can get the profits.

Meituan takeout used to have a gross margin of less than 20 per cent, while most physical dining has a gross margin of about 60 per cent.

Meituan takeout revenue and gross margin, cartography / finance

From 2015 to 2018, Meituan paid out $280 million, $5.14 billion, $18.32 billion and $30.52 billion to riders each year, mostly to Meituan, and a little to outsourced labor. At present, Meituan delivery platform is active more than 3 million riders, during the epidemic, Meituan delivery platform to recruit 75,000 new riders.

Like Jd.com, Meituan built its own delivery system, a vast and cumbersome infrastructure that ensured delivery efficiency and service experience for Meituan, but also became the largest cost item, dragging down earnings.

Delivery is also affected by the weather. Under extreme weather conditions such as rain and snow, Meituan needs to use a large amount of subsidies to motivate riders to pick up orders in order to complete the distribution task. In such a season, Meituan takeaway's loss will further widen.

In fact, Meituan's first-ever turnround came in the second quarter of 2019, helped in part by favorable weather. Take-out business profits, leading Meituan company in the second quarter officially turned a profit.

Raising the commission rate is the most effective way to speed up the realization. Meituan went public in Hong Kong in 2018, the year it made a sweeping change in its take-out commission rates, with many merchants increasing their fees from 15% to 20% , and in some cases from 20% to 26% . Businesses were overwhelmed.

In the eyes of the industry, the delivery industry is not ready for cash-in-hand. On the one hand, the platform on the business side of the digital transformation there is a lot of space, on the other hand Meituan and ele.me take-out war is not over.

From the increase in commission rates squeezed out of the profits, for the United States group of the market, after all, is a drop in the bucket.

Meituan is telling a story of economies of scale. Its internal logic is to minimize the platform's marginal cost by expanding its scale and optimizing operations, increasing the density of orders and distribution, and at the same time importing low-frequency but high-margin products and services, such as fresh wine tours, to the platform in a high-frequency and low-frequency band, increase the overall liquidity rate. So whether it is to do shopping, push unmanned distribution, or will Meituan distribution independent, Meituan is in fact in the script to do footnotes. And it is precisely because of this that Meituan is now able to make money.

The flip side of economies of scale is diseconomies of scale. That is, if the order density is not enough, then as the platform side Meituan, it will have to pay a high cost. This is also why Meituan take-out will be to merchants to take a guaranteed commission, because a 10-yuan order, Meituan is sure to lose.

To this day, low-margin takeout business is still Meituan's core business. While the company has a reputation for being borderless, it also has deals in group buying, wine tours, finance and even bike-sharing and ride-hailing, all of which extend beyond take-out.

Gross margin mapping of Meituan's business modules / finance

Hotels and liquor stores have a gross margin of 88% , but contribute only 20% to sales's business; a wide variety of new businesses, though growing fast, have gross margins lower than takeout, and most are still losing money. The unshakable status of take-out means the unshakable role of distribution as an infrastructure.

This is a paradox that has no short-term solution. "Meituan can't make money by raising commissions alone, but there's no easy way to do that in the short term. In the long run, it's all about scale and new business, " said one investor.

Binding and unbinding

"We should not focus on commission, but more on platform control and voice, " he said.

One worrying sign is the growing strength of Meituan takeout. In the third quarter of 2019, Meituan's takeaway sales accounted for 65.8 percent of total sales, far outpacing rival ele.me, according to the 2019 Q3 China Takeaway Industry Development Analysis released by Trustdata.

In February of this year, more than 170 members of the Nanchong Hotpot Association reported that Meituan has monopoly management problems.

From the market share point of view, China's current take-out pattern is not a monopoly. But an obvious fact is, no matter whether Meituan takeout or hungry, now all eyes on the supply side, trying to through a variety of means, businesses firmly tied to their own platform.

One or the other is the normal phenomenon of the industry. Meituan and ele.me will classify the merchants into strategic cooperative merchants and ordinary merchants according to the dimensions of brand, scale and trustworthiness, and will give different commission rates, exclusive merchants will get more resources to tilt.

The platform side will always offer something that is hard to say no to, but unacceptable. Liu said Meituan's marketing manager had repeatedly urged her to sign an exclusive contract and verbally promised that if she signed an exclusive contract, the commission rate would not rise in the future. Ele.me's marketing manager told her that she could offer her a large loan if she signed an exclusive deal with a certain amount of underwriting.

As a local brand merchant, Ms. Liu felt wooed and courted by the two platforms, but she was also wary that signing exclusive deals with either would offend the other. "It can be blocked by the other party, such as your store users can not search. Signing an exclusive is too risky. "

Liu knows not to be tied too closely to the platform, where customer resources and orders are in its hands. He turned down an exclusive, but couldn't turn down a platform.

In the mode of distribution, businesses can choose platform delivery, self-delivery, crowdsourcing delivery. In order to reduce dependence on the platform and earn a distribution fee, Liu tried his own distribution, but he didn't have enough people to do it, he couldn't keep up with orders, and his crowdsourced delivery orders were too small to negotiate prices. Either way, it's not as good as the platform.

A take-out on behalf of the operation of the personage told fuel finance and Economics, take-out platform main push is special delivery, if the business build logistics, the platform will give the business right, the weight of the ranking is: special delivery > Crowdsourcing > self-delivery.

Meituan delivered Meituan as an independent company in May last year, and ele.me will make its hummingbird independent the next month. Both platforms have already opened up their city-to-city logistics capacity, providing infrastructure functions on a large scale. "like water and electricity, you can't build it yourself, you have to use someone else's, " he said.

The much ballyhooed digital upgrade by Meituan and ele.me has indeed made the technology more efficient -- as if payment for delivery delays were automatic rather than manual. Meituan staff even gave her sales pos machine, in addition to the fast donkey purchase system, every aspect of the platform has been taken into account.

But at this time, she began to worry: "When I put all these machines installed, the future I will change it? "

As one of six million businesses, the increased competition is real. Take advertising. Ding Sheng's meituan stores, for example, cost 10,000 yuan a month to advertise, and "order very little without buying a ranking, which has become a fixed expense. "

The growth in advertising costs, which Meituan would like to see, is a healthier profit model than commission.

Meituan Business Revenue Growth Mapping / finance

MEITUAN's online marketing services revenues nearly tripled from 1.5 billion yuan in the first quarter of 2018 to 4.4 billion yuan in the third quarter of 2019, outpacing the growth in commissions.

"For businesses, Commission is passive after all, " says one investor. "But buying ads is active, and the results are statistically straightforward, and businesses are certainly more receptive. "

The control power of the platform is strengthening ceaselessly, the businessman also deepens ceaselessly to the platform's dependence. "Meituan and ele.me are getting worse and worse, " a fast-food restaurant owner in Shandong province told Caijing. "In general, our profits are much thinner. ".

But he chose to stay in Meituan. Because, although the profit of take-away is thin, but did increment on the basis of canning, it is the extra money that earns. "I may only make two dollars on a take-out order, but I'm willing to make it because if I cut the take-out, my store might lose money. "

"I don't do it unless I can no longer afford to pay for it, " the fast-food owner said.

In Ding Sheng's view, takeout has gone from an initial attempt to increase profits to being a channel for brand promotion, a drain on offline dining. After much hesitation, he decided to focus on the dining room.

But that doesn't mean takeout is out of the question. Ding Sheng has a take away shop nearby that is doing well even at a 20% rate. Because hundreds of orders can be made every day, the order density is high enough.

In any case, the epidemic is acting as a catalyst for restaurant operators to pay more attention to online operations, product quality, service quality. And these, will become the basis of a new round of take-out war in the future.

* The title is from Pexels. At the request of the interviewees, Ding Sheng and Chan were given pseudonyms.
